<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,151,679]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Etymology. This species is named 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blahnik &amp; Holzenthal" authorityYear="2011" box="[589,741,620,644]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Mortoniella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hystricosa">
<emphasis box="[589,741,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">M. hystricosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Latin word 
<emphasis box="[983,1059,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">hystrix</emphasis>
, a porcupine, and referring to the spiny apex of the dorsal phallic spine of the male in this species.
</paragraph>
